{ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6IZNJS8UcB8 }
1. e4 d5 2. d4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 { The only good move. } 4. f3 { Same as Von Hennig, in fact if they play c6 we play Bc4 and it transposes (before or after exfc3) } 4... exf3 5. Nxf3 Bg4 { Most common. } 6. h3 Bxf3 { Fifty fifty. } 7. Qxf3 Qxd4 8. Qxb7 Qe5+ 9. Be2 Qg3+ 10. Kf1 e6 11. Qxa8 Bc5 12. Qf3 { Taking the knight would be awful! } *


