1. e4 d5 2. d4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 { The only good move. } 4. f3 { Same as Von Hennig, in fact if they play c6 we play Bc4 and it transposes (before or after exfc3) } 4... exf3 5. Nxf3 Bg4 { Most common. } 6. h3 Bh5 { Fify fifty. } 7. g4 Bg6 8. Ne5 e6 9. Bg2 { Restricting the bishop's escape options. Important move! } 9... c6 { Most common. } 10. h4 h5 11. Nxg6 fxg6 12. g5 Nd5 13. Nxd5 exd5 { Castling is apparently good! Qd3 too. } 14. O-O *


