1. e4 d5 2. d4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 { The only good move. } 4. f3 { Same as Von Hennig, in fact if they play c6 we play Bc4 and it transposes (before or after exfc3) } 4... exf3 5. Nxf3 e6 { Passive players do that. This helps us choose where to put our next piece. } 6. Bd3 Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. Qe1 b6 9. Qh4 Bb7 10. Bg5 { Black has some resources, but also many bad moves here (80% win rate). } 10... h6 11. Bxh6 gxh6 12. Qxh6 Nbd7 13. Ng5 Re8 14. Bh7+ Nxh7 15. Qxh7+ Kf8 *


